observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Management agreed to:

Implement priority programs under the Annual Investment/Development Plan for the 20% Development Fund according to the DILG and DBM Joint Memorandum Circular for optimal utilization;

Include PPAs charged under the continuing appropriation in the monitoring conducted by the City Planning and Development Coordinator;

Consider reprogramming or reverting to unappropriated surplus all savings from completed and unfeasible programs, following budgetary rules; and

Provide billboards for all projects, including ongoing ones to promote transparency in government fund utilization.

We recommended that the Management:
Maintain appropriate inventory levels of stocks to avoid expiration;
Maintain Stock Cards for Drugs and Medicines and Medical Supplies for proper monitoring of the stock levels;
Install inventory management system for inventory items, mainly the drugs and medicines;
Provide adequate and proper storage areas for supplies and medicines in Bayugan Community Hospital; and
Conduct regular inventory count of inventories.

We recommended that:

The Property Officer maintain updated Property Cards, which must contain all the required information indicated in the source documents to facilitate reconciliation between the actual physical inventory and the accounting records;

The Accountant and the GSO exert efforts to compare their respective records and verify/trace the unreconciled balances and prepare the necessary adjusting entries to correct any unrecorded/ erroneous recording of PPEs and come up with the correct balances of the accounts;

Physical count be scheduled earlier in the year, usually in July of every year, to give enough time for the Inventory Committee to prepare the RPCPPE and to reconcile the results thereof first, with the records of the GSO, and next with the Accounting Office and be able to come up with reliable balances of the accounts.; and

The GSO exert extra efforts to trace and find the lost PPE items and held accountable those custodians thereof based on the Acknowledgement Receipt of Equipment (ARE).

