We recommended that:

The City GSO should prepare and maintain stock/property card  as required under the regulations to facilitate reconciliation with the Accounting Office;

Reconciliation should be made by both Offices to ascertain the correctness of amounts per physical count and those presented in the financial statements;

Investigate the discrepancies noted to ensure agreement of amounts; and 

Accounting and GSO should have coordination to come up with correct account classification for easy reference and classification.

We recommend that:

The Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) should properly evaluate the completeness of Bidding Documents, Eligibility and Technical requirements and other documents (Section 37.2.3, of R.A. 9184) before recommending the award of contracts to the City Mayor;

The City Government shall enter into contract with the winning bidder, provided, that all documentary requirements  are complied with;

The City Accountant must require all pertinent documents before certifying the disbursement vouchers as to completeness of supporting documents in line with Section 4(6) of P.D. 1445 to avoid doubts on the legality, validity and propriety of transactions.

